title: [BUG] SKBitmap.Decode decodes BMP with biSizeImage = 0 incorrectly
body:
### Description

I have a few BMP files which are not decoded correctly.

As GitHub does not allow .bmp files, I will put the buffer of the raw data in the code section in a collapsed section.

The example is a 45x45 BMP image (so 2025 pixels), but only the pixels with index 1710 until the last pixel are in the decoded SKBitmap, everything else is set to `color = 0`. With other Bitmaps I tested the exact index when pixels begin to show up is different, but ~1700. The pixels which are in the decoded image are the correct ones, it's just that the first ~1700 pixels are missing.
